President Obama has announced his intention to nominate General Philip Breedlove as the next Supreme Allied Commander Europe (SACEUR) and Commander of U.S. European Command. General Breedlove has served in various assignments in the U.S. Air Force for over three decades, including in Germany, Italy, Spain, and South Korea. As Commander of U.S. Air Forces in Europe and NATO's Allied Air Command, he has established strong relationships with NATO allies. If confirmed by the Senate, General Breedlove will replace Admiral Jim Stavridis as the Supreme Allied Commander. President Obama expressed gratitude for Admiral Stavridis' service in strengthening the NATO Alliance.